The paper discusses the combination of deep neuroevolution and deep reinforcement learning algorithms for policy search, which are commonly used in the fields of machine learning and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and the use of policy search, which falls under the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
